\begin{MintedVerbatim}[commandchars=\\\{\}]
You are an expert evaluator of causal reasoning chains. Your task is to classify each step of a causal chain by its temporal complexity \PYGZhy{}\PYGZhy{} the richness of temporal reasoning required to infer the quantitative effect of that causal step on the time series.

Temporal complexity has two independent sub\PYGZhy{}components:
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{1.} Delay and duration of the causal effect
\PYG{+w}{  }\PYG{k}{2.} Periodicity: one\PYGZhy{}off event vs. recurring or compounding pattern

Levels:
  Straightforward: immediate effect, short and bounded duration, one\PYGZhy{}off event whose effect interval is easy to identify.
  Predictable: delayed effect (days to weeks), moderately variable duration, recurring but regular and predictable pattern (e.g. seasonal, weekly).
  Variable: long lag or cumulative, non\PYGZhy{}linear effect that unfolds over an extended trajectory, irregular or compounding recurrences that are hard to disentangle.

Output only valid JSON, no explanation.
\end{MintedVerbatim}
